Package: fixes
Type: Package
Title: Tools for Creating and Visualizing Fixed-Effects Event Study Models
Version: 0.7.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "Yosuke", "Abe",
      email = "yosuke.abe0507@gmail.com",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: Provides functions for creating, analyzing, and visualizing event study models using fixed-effects regression. Supports staggered adoption, multiple confidence intervals, flexible clustering, and panel/time transformations in a simple workflow. Features both static (ggplot2) and interactive (plotly) visualizations with dynamic confidence interval switching.
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports:
    dplyr,
    ggplot2,
    fixest,
    broom,
    tibble,
    rlang
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
Suggests:
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    haven,
    testthat,
    tidyr,
    plotly
VignetteBuilder: knitr
URL: https://github.com/yo5uke/fixes
BugReports: https://github.com/yo5uke/fixes/issues
